defs.docs: Event loop that drives Tokio I/O resources.

defs.name: Background
defs.docs: Handle to the reactor running on a background thread.

defs.name: Shutdown
defs.docs: Future that resolves when the reactor thread has shutdown.

defs.name: handle
defs.docs: Returns a reference to the reactor handle.

defs.name: shutdown_on_idle
defs.docs: Shutdown the reactor on idle.

defs.name: shutdown_now
defs.docs: Shutdown the reactor immediately

defs.name: forget
defs.docs: Run the reactor on its thread until the process terminates.

defs.name: PollEvented
defs.docs:
Associates an I/O resource that implements the [`std::io::Read`] and/or
 [`std::io::Write`] traits with the reactor that drives it.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Creates a new `PollEvented` associated with the default reactor.

defs.name: new_with_handle
defs.docs: Creates a new `PollEvented` associated with the specified reactor.

defs.name: get_ref
defs.docs:
Returns a shared reference to the underlying I/O object this readiness
 stream is wrapping.

defs.name: get_mut
defs.docs:
Returns a mutable reference to the underlying I/O object this readiness
 stream is wrapping.

defs.name: into_inner
defs.docs: Consumes self, returning the inner I/O object

defs.name: poll_read_ready
defs.docs: Check the I/O resource's read readiness state.

defs.name: clear_read_ready
defs.docs:
Clears the I/O resource's read readiness state and registers the current
 task to be notified once a read readiness event is received.

defs.name: poll_write_ready
defs.docs: Check the I/O resource's write readiness state.

defs.name: clear_write_ready
defs.docs:
Resets the I/O resource's write readiness state and registers the current
 task to be notified once a write readiness event is received.

defs.name: Registration
defs.docs: Associates an I/O resource with the reactor instance that drives it.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Create a new `Registration`.

defs.name: register
defs.docs: Register the I/O resource with the default reactor.

defs.name: deregister
defs.docs: Deregister the I/O resource from the reactor it is associated with.

defs.name: register_with
defs.docs: Register the I/O resource with the specified reactor.

defs.name: poll_read_ready
defs.docs: Poll for events on the I/O resource's read readiness stream.

defs.name: take_read_ready
defs.docs: Consume any pending read readiness event.

defs.name: poll_write_ready
defs.docs: Poll for events on the I/O resource's write readiness stream.

defs.name: take_write_ready
defs.docs: Consume any pending write readiness event.

defs.name: Reactor
defs.docs: The core reactor, or event loop.

defs.name: Handle
defs.docs: A reference to a reactor.

defs.name: Turn
defs.docs: Return value from the `turn` method on `Reactor`.

defs.name: SetFallbackError
defs.docs: Error returned from `Handle::set_fallback`.

defs.name: with_default
defs.value: fn <F, R> (handle: &Handle, enter: &mut Enter, f: F) -> R
defs.docs: Set the default reactor for the duration of the closure

defs.name: new
defs.docs:
Creates a new event loop, returning any error that happened during the
 creation.

defs.name: handle
defs.docs:
Returns a handle to this event loop which can be sent across threads
 and can be used as a proxy to the event loop itself.

defs.name: set_fallback
defs.docs: Configures the fallback handle to be returned from `Handle::default`.

defs.name: turn
defs.docs:
Performs one iteration of the event loop, blocking on waiting for events
 for at most `max_wait` (forever if `None`).

defs.name: is_idle
defs.docs: Returns true if the reactor is currently idle.

defs.name: background
defs.docs: Run this reactor on a background thread.
